    <main>      
        <section id="z-brief">
            <p>Zentella was an emerging beauty brand focused on ethics 
                and sustainability as much as it was on quality. In a 
                sea of mass-commercial products, I wanted to create 
                branding elements to give the website its 
                own personality while staying grassroots.</p>
            <div>
                <h3>Role</h3>
                <p><span class="small-caps" style="letter-spacing: 2px;">UI/UX</span> <br>
                    Illustrations<br>
                    <span class="small-caps" style="letter-spacing: 2px;">HTML/CSS/</span>Liquid</p>
            </div>
        </section>
        <hr>
        <section id="z-artwork">
            <h3>Artwork</h3>
            <p class="single-column">To build on the existing branding material and the 
                founder's own personality, I chose the theme words 
                quiet, feminine, and playful. Hand-drawn illustrations 
                provide a part of this feel: Free, loose forms keep 
                them personal rather than mechanical.</p>

            <figure id="gif-process">
                <div>
                    <div>
                        <p class="light">Sketch</p>
                        <img src="39f2ee67c31e7bc182b84c0358c16566">
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <p class="light">Final GIF</p>
                        <img src="6fd8c89e2427a843922c5430030a6d1f">
                    </div>
                </div>
            </figure>
            <p class="single-column">This GIF is meant to symbolize decomposition. Because 
                    Zentella's products have compostable packaging, it 
                    builds on the theme of sustainability, a core 
                    idea behind the brand.</p>

            <figure>
                <img src="040340626b1a562b5781e0f4d4bbc2ce">
                <figcaption>Flower icons impart environmentalism and natural 
                    ingredients. Simple silhouettes carry a freeform touch, 
                    and splotched colors give a sense of DIY creation.</figcaption>         
            </figure>
            <video id="z-home-page" autoplay="" loop="" muted="">
                <source src="8862dca2d6c8706982c7831cf12e2178" type="video/mp4">
                Recording of home page concept.
            </video>
        </section>
        <section id="z-typography">
            <h3>Typography</h3>
            <p class="single-column">Typography is one of my main considerations; in the 
                space of the page designated for "lorem ipsum â€¦," 
                it carries the voice of a brand, and styles the 
                page itself. For a feminine tone, I started my 
                search with female typographers and narrowed it 
                with other criteria listed in the caption below.</p>

                <figure>
                    <div>
                        <div>
                            <p><span class="sample-text">abcdefghijklmnop 123 AQ <i>abcdefghijklmnop</i></span><br>
                                Chaparral Pro - body</p>
                            <p><span class="sample-text ten-mincho">abcdefghijklmnop 123 AQ</span><br>
                                Ten Mincho - header</p>   
                        </div>

