                    <figcaption>I chose typefaces which were serifed 
                            and drawn with humanistic axes for a human 
                            touch. Both are smart, although Chaparral 
                            owes its name to relaxed California foothills, 
                            while Ten Mincho balances it with a more 
                            serious nature.</figcaption>
                </figure>
                
                    
                <p class="single-column">I believe typographic details matter 
                    - the balancing of light and heavier weights, emphasis 
                    with italics or drop-caps, paragraph indentations, 
                    and added visual interest to break up text. These small 
                    details lead to a lasting professional image.</p>
